As Sergio Aguero fired Manchester City into a 3-0 lead against Liverpool on Monday, the Argentine striker achieved the record for the best scoring rate for a player with a minimum of 15 goals in Premier League history.

Aguero had only been on the field for 23 seconds before he sprinted onto a through ball from Jesus Navas to score his second goal in as many Premier League games.

The 26-year-old now tops an impressive list of some of the Premier League's finest ever strikers with 54 goals every 113 minutes on the pitch.

